<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="sure-adj">sure <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /ʃʊə(r), ʃɔː(r)/    美 /ʃʊr/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-certain">1.★ <strong>[不用于名词前；无比较级变化] 肯定的；有把握的 (certain)：</strong></h4>
<p>反 unsure </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I think he is coming, but I’m not quite sure. 
我认为他会来，但我不太肯定。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>(be) sure about / of:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He is sure of success. 
他有把握成功。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>(be) sure +(that) / wh- 从句：</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I am sure that smoking harms you. 
我确信吸烟对你有害。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I haven’t been sure whether I should write to him or not. 
我还不确定要不要给他写信。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>一定会；准会：</strong></h4>
<ul>
<li>(be) sure to do sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Whenever you come, wherever you go, you’re sure to see some unforgettable events. 
无论你什么时候来，无论你去哪里，你一定会见到一些难忘的事。</p><footer>2009 全国</footer></div>

<ul>
<li>[用于祈使句] (be) sure (not) to do sth：</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Be sure not to touch anything in the lab. 
千万别碰实验室里的任何东西。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="for-sure">for sure</h3>
<p>1.<strong>[非正式用语] 肯定地；毫无疑问地：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Nobody knows for sure why and how dinosaurs disappeared from the earth in such a short time. 
没有人确切地知道恐龙为什么、又是怎样在这么短的时间内从地球上消失的。</p><footer>人教② – 4</footer></div>

<h3 id="make-sure">make sure</h3>
<p>1.<strong>弄清；查明；设法确保：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He arrived at the cinema early to <strong>make sure of</strong> a seat. 
为确保有座位，他早早地到了电影院。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We <strong>make sure</strong> (<strong>that</strong>) we take good care of students on campus. 
我们确保在校园里照顾好学生。</p><footer>译林① – 1</footer></div>

<h3 id="to-be-sure">to be sure</h3>
<p>1.<strong>诚然；固然：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She’s not perfect, to be sure, but she is pretty. 
她固然不是十全十美，但很漂亮。</p></div>

<h2 id="_3">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>The idea “happiness,” <strong><em>_</em></strong>_, will not sit still for easy definition.  （2014 江苏）<br />
A.to be rigid<br />
B.to be sure<br />
C.to be perfect<br />
D.to be fair  </li>
<li>— Are you going to take part in the speech contest?
—That’s <strong><em>_</em></strong>__sure. It’s too good an opportunity to miss.   （2011 重庆改）<br />
A.No problem!<br />
B.That’s for sure.<br />
C.Why me?<br />
D.Why bother?  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. B  2. for  </p></div>